The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Anti-doping policy to top agenda

Helsinki: Anti-doping policy and the naming of the 2009 World Championships? host city will top the agenda at the International Association of Athletics Federations (IAAF) council meeting in Helsinki this weekend. 

The 28-member council will hear a report from the world athletics body?s anti-doping task force, set up in the wake of the Athens Olympics. 

The task force is expected to make recommendations for changes in the IAAF?s anti-doping policies and procedures. 

The IAAF Council will also decide on the venue for the 2009 world championships with Berlin, Split and Valencia the candidate cities. 

Final presentations will be made on Saturday with a decision expected later that day. 

The World Championships will be held in Helsinki next year, returning to the site of the inaugural event in 1983, and in Osaka in 2007. 

